{
  "doc_id": "42197",
  "text": "The relationship between diabetes and increased AD and VaD risk has recently been discussed in several excellent reviews. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] The weight of evidence suggests that diabetes increases the risk of both AD and VaD, and that this risk occurs regardless of the age at which diabetes occurs. [CITATION_3] Risk-enhancing mechanisms include the effects of insulin resistance described above, hyperglycemiarelated increased advanced glycation end products, and oxidative stress, inflammation, and macrovascular and microvascular injury.",
